https://data.wprdc.org/dataset/arrest-data
For this project, I used the Pittsburgh Police Arrest dataset to compare arrest rates across neighborhoods, so I could get an idea of which areas might be safer.

Miles Klingman
mek346@pitt.edu
Data Set: https://data.wprdc.org/dataset/fire-incidents-in-city-of-pittsburgh
This data set convers all fire incidents in the city of Pittsburgh updates to 8/11/25. It includes the type of fire, the address of the fire, neighborhood it occured in, etc.


What is this about?
This is our final project of the University of Pittsburgh's CMPINF 0010 class, where we look at 3 datasets from the WPRDC which are related to one metric to determine the best neighborhood in Pittsburgh.
